      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PERFECT NIGHT (8) gets the nod in the last. She's a fairly progressive filly who got her maiden out of the way when last seen at Sale, backed into $1.85 there and just coming clear from a game runner-up. Fifth in the G2 Wakeful Stakes in the Spring says she'll relish the extra ground now and she can measure up to these exposed types. JUST JENNI (9) is racing consistently, just finding one better last time over this route. She maps for a sweet run on a moderate tempo and should look the winner at some point. MOZU MARCASSIN (2) doesn't win out of turn but is going quite well, just finding one better last time at Ballarat. Consider. IMPULSIVE REACTION (4) has upside off a narrow maiden win here over 1600m, coming from well back to score. He should relish the extra ground now but will need things to go his way up front. MY ROCA FELLA (1) did enough fresh and can improve.",
